<TITLE> Man dies in 'gunfight' with army in Rangamati </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, June 26 (bdnews24.com)A man was shot dead and another arrested on Friday in an alleged gunfight at Majarer Channel near Shubhlong Bazaar in Rangamati, police said. The dead, Tarun Kusum Chakma, 30, was the son of Shashimohon Master of Moitrinagar in Sadar Upazilla. The arrestee, Elin Chakma, 27, was a United People's Democratic Front (UPDF) activist, claimed a leader of the hill tract-based party. Superintendent of police Masudul Hassan said 10-12 gunmen went to Shubhalong Bazaar on an engine-boat at around 11am. Troops posted the bazaar camp reached the spot on prior information and were greeted by gunshots. Tarun was killed when the army returned fire, he added. Hasan said that the others escaped and that the dead body was sent to Rangamati General Hospital for autopsy. District coordinator of UPDF Shanti Dev Chakma told the reporters Elin Chakma was an activist of their organisation and arrested as he was chasing the terrorists. Dev demanded his unconditional release. bdnews2
